  "description": "Non-material amendment to planning permission LBI ref: P2013/4007/FUL dated 14/2/2014 for the ‘partial demolition, refurbishment and extensions [including a new fourth floor] to existing office building and change of use of part of the ground and basement floors from office use to flexible office or retail floorspace [falling within use classes B1, A1, A2 or A3] with the installation of roof plant, new pedestrian access, associated landscaping and cycle parking.’\r\n\r\nAmendments to include:\r\n\r\n- A change in the mullion spacing on the ground floor windows on City Road and Epworth Street- the central of the 3 panes of glass would be wider than the 2 to either side and the mullions would line up with mullions on upper windows to maintain the vertical emphasis.  On Tabernacle Street, 4 panes equal in width would be introduced.  The outer mullion of each window would line up with the mullions on above windows.\r\n- Extra mullions on the 1st, 2nd and 3rd floors of the Tabernacle Street elevation, and on 1st, 2nd and 3rd floors of eastern courtyard elevation.\r\n- Exposing the existing 3rd floor up- stand on the Epworth Street (south) and Tabernacle (east) Street elevations- painted black to match.\r\n- Revised glazing on Tabernacle Street elevation- lower sections of windows will be backpainted to ensure privacy to basement level rooms.\r\n- Plant enclosure would be introduced on the northwestern corner of the roof- clad in grey cementisious board\r\n- Infilling of corner of north west stairs with City Road underpass, in white render, to accommodate new plant for the retail element of the scheme.",
